[normal]Legal aid is both
[normal] a right in itself and an essential precondition for the exercise and enjoyment of a number of human rights, including the rights to a fair tr
[normal]ial and to an effective remedy. 
[normal] 
[normal]It represents an important safeguard that 
[normal]contributes to ensuring the fairness and public trust in 
[normal]the administration of justice.
[normal]Legal aid s
[normal]hould be as broad as possible...
[normal]to contribute to the elimination of obstacles and barriers that impair or restrict
[normal] access to justice by providing assistance to people otherwise unable to afford legal representation a
[normal]nd access to the court system.
