[normal] Tom Bingham, 
[normal]The Rule of Law
[normal], 
[normal]Allen Lane
[normal], 
[normal]London
[normal], 2010, pp. 85 and 88.  That the rule of law included a requirement on the State to furnish civil legal ai
[normal]d, in addition to protection for those accused of crimes was clear.  The rule of law includes that 
[normal]“means must be provided for resolving, without prohibitive cost or inordinate delay, bona fide civil disputes which the parties themselves are unable to reso
[normal]lve”.
[normal]   That the principles of the common law protect the right of access to justice, including through the testing of rules which might inhibit access to the court is clear.  See 
[normal]R v Lord Chancellor ex p Witham 
[normal][1998] QB 575 (this case dealt with the impl
[normal]ications of court fees for access to the courts).  
